text: Kim Min-seong (born 3 December 1994) is a South Korean bobsledder. She competed in the two-woman event at the 2018 Winter Olympics. ==References== Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:South Korean female bobsledders Category:Olympic bobsledders of South Korea Category:Bobsledders at the 2018 Winter Olympics Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
